    "recap_headline": "University of St. Thomas Athletics",
    "recap_text": "GREELEY,\u00a0COLO.-\nSt. Thomas baseball splits the first series of Summit League play against the Northern Colorado Bears.\u00a0The\u00a0Tommies\u00a0took game one 8-5 before falling\nGame One:\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0struck first in the top half of the first inning when\nLucas McNellis\npunched it through the\u00a0right-side scoring Recchio from third.\nNorthern Colorado then hit back-to-back solo homeruns in the bottom of the second to take a 2-1 lead.\nOwen Bond\nthen knotted the game at two when he\u00a0brought in\nZan Von Schlegell\nin the top of the third.\nThe Bears then plated two in the bottom of the second, taking a 4-2 lead.\nSt. Thomas responded quickly in the top of the seventh when\nOwen Bond\ntripled to start the inning and was brought\u00a0in off an RBI from\nJoe Roder\n.\nRoder\u00a0came up big in the top of the eighth when his RBI double drove in two\u00a0Tommies\u00a0and gave the\u00a0Purple\u00a0a 5-4 lead.\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0added\u00a0three\u00a0in\u00a0the ninth off an error by Northern Colorado and a\nSean Marlow\nRBI single.\nNorthern Colorado\u00a0plated one in the bottom of the ninth to make the final score 8-5.\nGame Two:\nSt. Thomas struck first once again, this time plating two in the top of the first. McNellis and\nMax Berrisford\npicked up RBIs. Recchio and Puder crossed the plate for the Purple.\nNorthern Colorado then\u00a0scored\u00a0in the bottom half to cut the deficit to one.\u00a0The Bears then\u00a0knotted the game at two in the second of a solo home run.\nEaston Fritcher\nmade the score 4-2 with a two out RBI double in the third.\nThe Bears quickly\u00a0responded,\u00a0scoring two of their own in the bottom half of the third,\u00a0knotting\u00a0the game at four.\nNorthern Colorado broke the tie in the seventh when they scored two. The Bears scored three more in the bottom of the eighth,\u00a0taking \u00a09-4 lead.\nUp Next:\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0will remain in Colorado to take on Air Force, Monday, March 16th. First pitch is set for 2 p.m. CT.\nFollow Along:\nAny and all information\u00a0pertaining to\u00a0the St. Thomas baseball team can be found at tommiesports.com and on Twitter @TommieBase and Instagram at @TommieBaseball."
